quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  27,67,"Those who disbelieve say, “When we have become dust, and our ancestors, shall we be brought out"
  27,68,"We were promised that before, we and our ancestors—these are nothing but legends of the ancients.”"
  27,69,"Say, travel through the earth, and observe the fate of the guilty.”"
  27,70,"But do not grieve over them, and do not be troubled by what they plot"
  27,71,"And they say, “When is this promise, if you are truthful?”"
  27,72,"Say, “Perhaps some of what you are impatient for has drawn near.”"
  27,73,"Your Lord is gracious towards humanity, but most of them are not thankful"
  27,74,"And your Lord knows what their hearts conceal, and what they reveal"
  27,75,"There is no mystery in the heaven and the earth, but it is in a Clear Book"
  27,76,This Quran relates to the Children of Israel most of what they differ about
  27,77,And it is guidance and mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Your Lord will judge between them by His wisdom. He is the Almighty, the All-Knowing"
  27,79,So rely on God. You are upon the clear truth
  27,80,"You cannot make the dead hear, nor can you make the deaf hear the call if they turn their backs and flee"
  27,81,"Nor can you guide the blind out of their straying. You can make no one listen, except those who believe in Our verses; for they are Muslims"
  27,82,"And when the Word has fallen on them, We will bring out for them from the earth a creature which will say to them that the people are uncertain of Our revelations"